sql: SQL statement
	description=The question or command you type.
parser: Parser
	description=The part that reads your words and figures out what you mean.
vdbe: VDBE
	description=The worker that follows the step-by-step plan.
btree: B-tree storage
	description=The place where SQLite keeps rows and indexes in neat order.
pager: Pager
	description=The part that brings pieces of the database in and out of memory and disk.
